Create a Lambda Function:

Go to the AWS Management Console and navigate to the Lambda service.
Click on "Create function."
Choose "Container image" as the option for the runtime.
Enter a name for your function and select the ECR repository and image that you pushed earlier.
Configure the function as needed (e.g., memory, timeout, etc.).
Click on "Create function."
Test the Lambda Function:

In the Lambda console, click on your function to open it.
Click on "Test" in the top right corner.
Create a new test event (you can use a sample event template).
Click on "Test" to invoke the Lambda function with the test event.
View the results in the "Execution result" tab to see if your function executed successfully.
